osing this gap in the literature and investigates the urban multilingual practices in Moscow. A particular focus is placed on the investigation of multimodal interactions within minority groups. Ideologies about language play an important role in how communities form and differentiate themselves from others. Interestingly, the book unearths significant ideological views held about language varieties spoken in Moscow. The collection offers interdisciplinary contributions from areas such as education, intercultural communication, migration studies, geography, ethnography of communication, and community practitioners. In sum, the reader benefits from an insightful introduction to the complex linguistic situation in the dynamic capital of Russia.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aIdentität. 4aMehrsprachigkeit. 4aRussland. 4aSprachpolitik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aMoscow Multilingualism, Russian Language Policy, Minority Language Education, Identity.1 aAfanasieva, Arina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAli-zade, Pavel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaranova, Vlada, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergelson, Mira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergelson, Mira, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBurdygina, Margarita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDemintseva, Ekaterina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFedorova, Kapitolina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrabarnik, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKade, Madina, econtributor.4ct